postcontent:
My next Illinois Concealed Carry class will be offered on Saturday and Sunday, July 18-19, 2015. The first day (7/18) will be the NRA Basic Pistol Class and the second day (7/19) will be the Illinois-specific material, to include a shooting session. I teach the classroom portion of the class in my large, comfortably furnished basement. We have very comfortable seating in a media room that includes a 63' display for computer projection, as well as plenty of space for holster work and learning the fundamentals of pistol shooting using the SIRT guns. I also use a computerized shot reporting system that provides instant, real-time feedback on your shot placement using the SIRT guns. I'll provide the address upon registration.

You need an Illinois FOID to attend this class and, upon successful completion of the course, will receive both the Basic Pistol and the Illinois course completion certifications. We will also cover how to apply online to the Illinois State Police website to submit a concealed carry license application.

Vision and hearing protection are required for Day 2, as well as a concealable pistol with a minimum of 50-rounds of ammunition. We will shoot at Gat Guns in East Dundee, IL. If you do not currently own a pistol, you may rent a pistol from Gat Guns for the shooting portion of the class.

The cost for the course is $150 per person, with a $50 non-refundable deposit paid in case of no-show upon registration. Range fee (approximately $21) and any needed gun rental is additional and payable directly to Gat Guns.

Please RSVP for the course at the following link: http://www.ccw-usa.com/schedule
